(24, 1, '2012-11-08 12:57:31', '2012-11-08 08:57:31', 'Founder''s Day is commemorated every year on September 13, the day Claude Martin died. Some of the traditions of this day include an extended formal assembly in the morning with a faculty march, a speech by a prominent guest or alumnus, the playing of bagpipes, singing of the school song and other selected hymns by the College choir, and the laying of a wreath at Claude Martin''s tomb. For the Founder''s Day dinner the entire senior school and staff are treated to an elaborate sit-down dinner in the afternoon. Claude Martin had apparently listed in his will that his death should not be commemorated as a day of mourning but one of celebration of his life. He had also written out a menu for the meal to be served. Although today, the menu does not remain the same, the tradition of the Founder''s Day dinner is still preserved. A Founder''s Day Social is held in the evening for the senior school. Classes are suspended on Founder''s Day, which is generally followed by a school holiday.', 'Celebrating Founder''s Day', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'celebrating-founders-day', '', '', '2012-11-08 12:57:31', '2012-11-08 08:57:31', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wpsite/?p=24', 0, 'post', '', 1),
